{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":976,"text":"As a conceptual artist,"},{"time":2394,"text":"I'm constantly looking for creative ways\nto spark challenging conversations."},{"time":6726,"text":"I do this though painting, sculpture,\nvideo and performance."},{"time":10449,"text":"But regardless of the format,"},{"time":11912,"text":"two of my favorite materials\nare history and dialogue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":15796,"text":"In 2007, I created \"Lotus,\""},{"time":18259,"text":"a seven-and-a-half-foot diameter,"},{"time":20057,"text":"600-pound glass depiction\nof a lotus blossom."},{"time":23937,"text":"In Buddhism, the lotus is a symbol\nfor transcendence"},{"time":27430,"text":"and for purity of mind and spirit."},{"time":29882,"text":"But a closer look at this lotus"},{"time":32327,"text":"reveals each petal\nto be the cross-section of a slave ship."},{"time":35985,"text":"This iconic diagram was taken\nfrom a British slaving manual"},{"time":39684,"text":"and later used by abolitionists to show\nthe atrocities of slavery."},{"time":44104,"text":"In America, we don't like\nto talk about slavery,"},{"time":46533,"text":"nor do we look at it as a global industry."},{"time":49397,"text":"But by using this Buddhist symbol,"},{"time":51049,"text":"I hope to universalize and transcend"},{"time":53676,"text":"the history and trauma of black America"},{"time":56089,"text":"and encourage discussions\nabout our shared past."}]},{"cues":[{"time":60033,"text":"To create \"Lotus,\"\nwe carved over 6,000 figures."},{"time":64469,"text":"And this later led to a commission\nby the City of New York"},{"time":67216,"text":"to create a 28-foot version in steel"},{"time":69494,"text":"as a permanent installation\nat the Eagle Academy for Young Men,"},{"time":72960,"text":"a school for black and latino students,"},{"time":75122,"text":"the two groups most affected\nby this history."},{"time":78244,"text":"The same two groups are very affected\nby a more recent phenomenon,"},{"time":81819,"text":"but let me digress."}]},{"cues":[{"time":83840,"text":"I've been collecting\nwooden African figures"},{"time":86031,"text":"from tourist shops and flea markets\naround the world."},{"time":88539,"text":"The authenticity and origin\nof them is completely debatable,"},{"time":91645,"text":"but people believe these\nto be imbued with power,"},{"time":94327,"text":"or even magic."},{"time":95683,"text":"Only recently have I figured out\nhow to use this in my own work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":99412,"text":"(Gun shots)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":113253,"text":"Since 2012, the world has witnessed\nthe killings of Trayvon Martin,"},{"time":117445,"text":"Michael Brown, Eric Garner,\nSandra Bland, Tamir Rice"},{"time":121209,"text":"and literally countless other\nunarmed black citizens"},{"time":124193,"text":"at the hands of the police,"},{"time":125646,"text":"who frequently walk away\nwith no punishment at all."},{"time":128775,"text":"In consideration of these victims"},{"time":130828,"text":"and the several times that even I,"},{"time":132662,"text":"a law-abiding, Ivy League professor,"},{"time":135159,"text":"have been targeted and harassed\nat gunpoint by the police."},{"time":138647,"text":"I created this body of work\nsimply entitled \"BAM.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":144389,"text":"It was important to erase\nthe identity of each of these figures,"},{"time":147912,"text":"to make them all look the same\nand easier to disregard."},{"time":151685,"text":"To do this, I dip them in a thick,\nbrown wax"},{"time":153909,"text":"before taking them to a shooting range"},{"time":155896,"text":"where I re-sculpted them using bullets."},{"time":159098,"text":"And it was fun,"},{"time":160303,"text":"playing with big guns and\nhigh-speed video cameras."},{"time":163164,"text":"But my reverence for these figures\nkept me from actually pulling the trigger,"},{"time":166845,"text":"somehow feeling as if I would\nbe shooting myself."},{"time":169995,"text":"Finally, my cameraman, Raul,\nfired the shots."},{"time":174503,"text":"I then took the fragments of these"},{"time":176396,"text":"and created molds,\nand cast them first in wax,"},{"time":180749,"text":"and finally in bronze\nlike the image you see here,"},{"time":183876,"text":"which bears the marks\nof its violent creation"},{"time":186004,"text":"like battle wounds or scars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":188583,"text":"When I showed this work recently in Miami,"},{"time":190615,"text":"a woman told me she felt\nevery gun shot to her soul."},{"time":193424,"text":"But she also felt that these artworks"},{"time":196039,"text":"memorialized the victims of these killings"},{"time":198063,"text":"as well as other victims of\nracial violence throughout US history."}]},{"cues":[{"time":201812,"text":"But \"Lotus\" and \"BAM\" are larger\nthan just US history."},{"time":204870,"text":"While showing in Berlin last year,"},{"time":206758,"text":"a philosophy student asked me\nwhat prompted these recent killings."},{"time":210343,"text":"I showed him a photo\nof a lynching postcard"},{"time":212985,"text":"from the early 1900s"},{"time":214374,"text":"and reminded him that these killings\nhave been going on for over 500 years."},{"time":219922,"text":"But it's only through questions like his"},{"time":221852,"text":"and more thoughtful dialogue\nabout history and race"},{"time":224718,"text":"can we evolve as individuals and society."}]},{"cues":[{"time":227709,"text":"I hope my artwork creates a safe space"},{"time":230566,"text":"for this type of honest exchange"},{"time":233002,"text":"and an opportunity for people\nto engage one another"},{"time":235765,"text":"in real and necessary conversation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":238751,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":239925,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}